{
  "id": "L15",
  "title": "At the Doctor's Office",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome! In this lesson, you'll learn the essential phrases for visiting a doctor (`il dottore`) in Italy."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V01",
      "data": {
        "Il dottore": "The doctor"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Buongiorno",
        "meaning": "Good morning / Good day"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V02",
      "data": {
        "Un appuntamento": "An appointment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V03",
      "data": {
        "Ho": "I have"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Ho comes from the verb 'avere' (to have). It's the form for 'io' (I). The 'h' is silent!"
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ho un appuntamento",
        "meaning": "I have an appointment"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V04",
      "data": {
        "Il problema": "The problem"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V05",
      "data": {
        "Mal di testa": "Headache"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ho mal di testa",
        "meaning": "I have a headache"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V06",
      "data": {
        "Da": "For / Since"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V07",
      "data": {
        "Tre giorni": "Three days"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "giorni",
        "phonetic": "jòr-ni",
        "tip": "The 'gi' sound in Italian is like the 'j' in 'job'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S01",
      "title": "Checking In",
      "setting": "You've arrived at the clinic. First, you'll speak to the receptionist, then to the doctor.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the receptionist and state you have an appointment",
          "chatbot_message": "Buongiorno. Mi dica."
        },
        {
          "title": "Explain your main symptom to the doctor",
          "chatbot_message": "Va bene. Si accomodi, prego. ... Buongiorno. Qual è il problema?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say how long you have had this problem",
          "chatbot_message": "Capisco. Da quanto tempo?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now the doctor will ask for more details. Let's learn how to add more information."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V08",
      "data": {
        "Anche": "Also"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V09",
      "data": {
        "La febbre": "The fever"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ho anche la febbre",
        "meaning": "I also have a fever"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In Italian, it's common to say 'ho LA febbre' (I have THE fever), using the article 'la'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V10",
      "data": {
        "Dove": "Where"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V11",
      "data": {
        "Qui": "Here"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mi fa male qui",
        "meaning": "It hurts here"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V12",
      "data": {
        "Ho preso": "I have taken"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "'Ho preso' is a common way to talk about a past action. It's formed with 'ho' (I have) + 'preso' (taken)."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V13",
      "data": {
        "Il paracetamolo": "The paracetamol"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S02",
      "title": "Describing Symptoms",
      "setting": "The conversation with the doctor continues. He is asking more questions about your condition.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Describe another symptom",
          "chatbot_message": "Ok, grazie. C'è altro?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Answer where it hurts",
          "chatbot_message": "Capisco. Dove le fa male?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tell the doctor what you have already taken",
          "chatbot_message": "Ok. Ha preso qualcosa?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Excellent. The doctor will now give you advice. If you don't understand, it's okay to ask them to repeat!"
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V14",
      "data": {
        "Può": "You can (formal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V15",
      "data": {
        "Ripetere": "To repeat"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V16",
      "data": {
        "Lentamente": "Slowly"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Può ripetere, per favore?",
        "meaning": "Can you repeat, please?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To be more specific, you can add 'più' to say 'more slowly': 'Può ripetere più lentamente?'"
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V17",
      "data": {
        "Ho bisogno di": "I need"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L15_V18",
      "data": {
        "Una ricetta": "A prescription"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L15_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "ricetta",
        "phonetic": "ri-chét-ta",
        "tip": "The 'ce' in 'ricetta' sounds like the 'che' in 'check'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ho bisogno di una ricetta?",
        "meaning": "Do I need a prescription?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L15_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Grazie mille",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L15_S03",
      "title": "Understanding Advice",
      "setting": "The doctor has finished the examination and is giving you advice.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask the doctor to repeat their advice slowly",
          "chatbot_message": "Bene. Deve bere molta acqua e stare a riposo per due giorni."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if you need a prescription",
          "chatbot_message": "Certo. Deve... bere... molta... acqua. E... stare... a... riposo."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the doctor for their time",
          "chatbot_message": "No, non serve. Solo il paracetamolo va bene."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}